Kibwezi West MP Patrick Musimba, his wife Angela Mwende and three others charged with stealing Sh1.15 billion from Chase Bank, were yesterday released on bond. The Musimbas are facing the charges alongside the bankâ€™s chairman Mohamed Khan and employees Duncan Kabui, James Mwenja and Makrios Agumbi. The suspects were released on a Sh10 million bond each with sureties of like sums and alternative cash bails of Sh2 million each. Musimba was required to deposit an additional bond of Sh30 million and alternatively cash bail of Sh5 million for his two companies - Porting Access Limited and Itec Limited. The parties will return to the court on December 10 for pretrial to confirm supply of trail documents and set hearing dates. Click here for the latest political news